## View Layer Update

Files created/modified:
- Added include/View/FloatingText.h and src/View/FloatingText.cpp
- Added include/View/EnemyStatusRenderer.h and src/View/EnemyStatusRenderer.cpp
- Added include/View/ElementalFX.h and src/View/ElementalFX.cpp
- Added include/View/UIHelpers.h
- Added include/View/HUDView.h and src/View/HUDView.cpp
- Added include/View/ResultView.h and src/View/ResultView.cpp
- Added include/View/InventoryView.h and src/View/InventoryView.cpp (grid UI + ObservableList attach)
- Added include/View/MenuView.h and src/View/MenuView.cpp (menu highlight)
- Added src/View/ControllerIntegrationExample.cpp (documentation only)
- Modified include/View/EntityRenderer.h and src/View/EntityRenderer.cpp to support UpdateSpriteRect, SetEntityVisible, GetEntityPtr
- Modified include/View/ParticleRenderer.h and src/View/ParticleRenderer.cpp to support EmitBurst and debris rendering
- Modified include/View/GameView.h and src/View/GameView.cpp for dual-world layer + shadow shader, floating text, enemy status, result view integration
- Modified include/View/CharacterRenderer.h and src/View/CharacterRenderer.cpp to support Elemental tint, PlayAction, Pet defaults, and aura sprite rendering
- Modified include/View/EnemyStatusRenderer.h and src/View/EnemyStatusRenderer.cpp to load atlas sprite frames for status icons
- Modified src/main.cpp → runnable smoke test with all views
- Added assets/shaders/shadow.vs and assets/shaders/shadow.fs (dual-world post-process)

What changed and why:
- InventoryView: art-driven grid UI with snapshot API, controller-owned selection, plus AttachObservable for ObservableList<const Item*> auto-update
- MenuView: passive menu rendering; Update(selectedIndex) highlights current selection
- FloatingText: Emit large short-lived text in world coords; Update/Render
- EnemyStatusRenderer: uses atlas frames (status/burn, status/wet, status/shocked) when available; fallback text icons; emits floating text on status set
- ElementalFX: per-entity DamageType tint; CharacterRenderer uses tint in SubmitSprite and renders aura frames behind character when atlas has aura/ elements
- CharacterRenderer: PlayAction method for precise attack/hurt/skill animation switching; register defaults for Pet type (idle/walk/attack/dead); stores entity->atlas map for aura queries
- ParticleRenderer: EmitBurst helper creates short-lived view-managed debris; RenderAll now advances and draws it
- GameView: supports SetActiveWorldLayer(WorldLayer, lightPos) — applies shadow shader for Shadow layer; integrates all view components (floating text, enemy status, entity, result, menu rendering)
- EntityRenderer: UpdateSpriteRect (chest open), SetEntityVisible (fake wall destroy), GetEntityPtr accessor for other view components
- Shaders: shadow.fs darkens screen except circular light around player position
- main.cpp: full smoke test with keyboard controls (M=menu, I=inventory, S=results, F=particles, arrows=menu)

Status:
- All changes are confined to the View folder and related headers. Controllers/models must call the view APIs to display statuses, floating text, play actions, swap chest frames, and trigger debris emissions.
